{"questionId":"32383414","questionHtml":"<p>Find the two possible values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>YZ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 COSINE RULE<br></strong>attempt to substitute into cosine rule to form a quadratic for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>YZ</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>9</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>YZ</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04503</mn><msup><mo>…</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04503</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mi>YZ</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>YZ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>185</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>184692</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52739</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>191</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>191313</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> s.f. values.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 SINE RULE</strong><br>attempt to substitute into sine rule to find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>04503</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>41</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7597</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>138</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>240</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>103</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>240</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>75972</mn><mo>…</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <strong>A1</strong> for any of these angles seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>YZ</mi><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Z</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>35</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>YZ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>185</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>184692</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>53</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>52739</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32383414","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.4e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the two possible values of YZ.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.8—Unit circle, Pythag identity, solving trig equations graphically"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}